# Bridge Seoul

Bridge Seoul helps foreign visitors search Korean local places in English, converts intent into Korean NAVER local search queries, and opens the result in NAVER Map.

## Local Run

Create `.env`:

```env
NAVER_SEARCH_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
NAVER_SEARCH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
PORT=8787
HOST=127.0.0.1
```

Run:

```bash
set -a
source .env
set +a
python3 server.py
```

Open:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8787
```

## External Deployment

Use a server host such as Render, Railway, or Fly.io. Static-only hosts will not work by themselves because NAVER Search API needs a server-side secret.

Required environment variables:

```text
HOST=0.0.0.0
NAVER_SEARCH_CLIENT_ID=your_client_id
NAVER_SEARCH_CLIENT_SECRET=your_client_secret
```

Render can use `render.yaml` directly.

Health check:

```text
/health
```

## Security

Do not commit `.env`.

The current NAVER Client Secret was exposed in chat during setup. Regenerate it in NAVER Developers before public deployment.

